        </profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="545" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d545">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Potsdam/7–1245: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 545<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Secretary of War</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SHL1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Aboard</hi> USS “<hi rend="smallcaps">Augusta</hi>”</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-12">July 12, 1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Your Number 95.<note n="1" xml:id="d545fn1">
                        <ref target="#d543">Document No. 543</ref>.</note>)</p>
                <p>The President agrees that his directive should be liberally interpreted so as to
                    permit the furnishing of supplies and equipment within the limits of previous
                    commitments to forces which make possible the redeployment of American forces
                    from other theatres to participate in the war against <persName corresp="#p_J1">Japan</persName>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
